<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="152" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Material examined.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="152">
RUSSIA, Altai Republic, Kosh-Agach District: 3♂ (ISEA), Karagemskyi Mt. Range (
<geoCoordinate direction="north" orientation="latitude" precision="925" value="49.866665">49°52'N</geoCoordinate>
; 
<geoCoordinate direction="east" orientation="longitude" precision="925" value="87.11667">87°07'E</geoCoordinate>
), 2500-2900 m, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“kurums”">&quot;kurums&quot;</normalizedToken>
(=scree formed by huge boulders) and alpine meadow, 27.06.2014 (A.A. Fomichev); 1♀ (ISEA), Karagem River valley (
<geoCoordinate direction="north" orientation="latitude" precision="925" value="49.883335">49°53'N</geoCoordinate>
; 
<geoCoordinate direction="east" orientation="longitude" precision="925" value="87.183334">87°11'E</geoCoordinate>
), 1360 m, stony steppe slope, 28.06.2014 (A.A. Fomichev); KAZAKHSTAN, East Kazakhstan Area: 1♂ (holotype of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Acantholycosa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Acantholycosa katunensis" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="katunensis">Acantholycosa katunensis</taxonomicName>
